		<exercise>
			<title>Multinomial Theorem</title>
			<idx><h>Multinomial Theorem</h></idx>
			<statement>
				<p>
Prove the multinomial theorem
<me>
(x_1 + x_2 + \cdots + x_s)^n = \sum_{n_1 + n_2 + \cdots + n_s = n} { n \choose n_1, n_2, \ldots, n_s} x_1^{n_1} x_2^{n_2}
 \cdots x_s^{n_s} 
</me>
where
<me>
	{ n \choose n_1, n_2, \ldots, n_s} = \frac{n!}{n_1! \, n_2! \, \cdots, \, n_s !}.
</me>




				</p>
			</statement>
